WEBVTT

00:06.881 --> 00:08.466
- Who wants to ring the bell?

00:08.508 --> 00:11.469
- Pleased to meet you, Jan.

00:11.511 --> 00:13.138
I'm Bob.

00:14.097 --> 00:15.140
- Fromage.

00:15.181 --> 00:17.058
[laughter]

00:17.100 --> 00:19.936
- [softly]
You are unforgettable.

00:19.978 --> 00:24.149
You remember that stuff
you did with the other boys?

00:25.817 --> 00:28.653
<i>[quiet music]</i>

00:28.695 --> 00:30.697
<i>- Berchtold went</i>
<i>and took Jan horseback riding,</i>

00:30.739 --> 00:33.742
and they were supposed
to be back some time ago.

00:36.202 --> 00:38.121
<i>- You have been chosen.</i>

00:38.163 --> 00:40.040
<i>You will have special child</i>

00:40.081 --> 00:42.167
<i>with male companion.</i>

00:42.208 --> 00:44.377
<i>You have been chosen...</i>

00:44.419 --> 00:46.963
- They said their names
were Zada and Zethra.

00:47.005 --> 00:48.548
- And what do they want?

00:48.590 --> 00:51.009
<i>- The only way</i>
<i>that he would consider</i>

00:51.051 --> 00:54.471
bringing Jan back
is to marry her.

00:56.097 --> 00:58.308
- Peter Welsh, FBI.

00:58.933 --> 01:02.687
We tracked him to a hotel
in MazatlÃ¡n, Mexico.

01:02.729 --> 01:05.440
- So Zada said they are going
to be watching us all the time.

01:05.482 --> 01:07.734
They're gonna look like
regular people, okay?

01:07.776 --> 01:11.279
This is a reminder
of the mission.

01:12.655 --> 01:14.866
- Sue!

01:14.908 --> 01:16.576
- Jan.

01:25.335 --> 01:28.588
<i>[haunting rhythmic music]</i>

01:28.630 --> 01:31.633
<i>* *</i>

01:48.817 --> 01:51.486
<i>- They're gonna look like</i>
<i>regular people.</i>

01:57.992 --> 01:59.494
- Mary Ann.

02:01.663 --> 02:04.165
I'm so glad Jan
and Brother Berchtold

02:04.207 --> 02:05.291
were found safe.

02:05.333 --> 02:08.169
- Oh, that's kind.

02:08.211 --> 02:10.005
- Everyone knew
he'd never hurt her.

02:10.046 --> 02:12.632
The newspapers
are just ridiculous these days.

02:12.674 --> 02:14.884
I just hope
they bring him home soon.

02:14.926 --> 02:18.013
A manic depressive
does not belong in jail.

02:18.054 --> 02:21.307
- If only it were
all that simple.

02:21.349 --> 02:24.185
<i>[faint static sounds]</i>

02:28.023 --> 02:31.317
<i>[soft music]</i>

02:31.359 --> 02:38.324
<i>* *</i>

02:43.872 --> 02:44.914
[door clicks open]

02:44.956 --> 02:46.708
- Hi there, Jan.

02:46.750 --> 02:47.792
Nice to meet you.

02:47.834 --> 02:49.919
[door clicks shut]

02:49.961 --> 02:54.883
So...been watching anything fun
on television lately?

02:55.383 --> 02:57.010
- "I Dream of Jeannie."

02:57.052 --> 02:58.762
- Mm-hmm.

02:58.803 --> 03:00.347
Oh, yeah.

03:00.388 --> 03:02.432
My girls love that too.

03:02.474 --> 03:03.892
[laughs softly]

03:05.560 --> 03:07.354
All right, looks good.

03:07.395 --> 03:10.565
Healthy and normal.

03:10.607 --> 03:15.028
Now I'm going to ask you
some questions about Mexico,

03:15.070 --> 03:18.698
and there are no wrong answers,

03:18.740 --> 03:22.369
but it's important
that you be honest, okay?

03:24.496 --> 03:29.000
Now, did Mr. Berchtold
ever touch you,

03:29.042 --> 03:31.461
touch your body
under your clothes or expose...

03:31.503 --> 03:32.962
[voice fades]

03:33.004 --> 03:36.299
[soft rustling sound]

03:36.341 --> 03:39.219
Jan?

03:39.260 --> 03:43.640
Is there anything you remember
or would like to tell me?

03:44.349 --> 03:45.767
- No.

03:47.811 --> 03:51.523
- All right, well, I'd like
to move to the pelvic exam now.

03:51.564 --> 03:53.441
Just lay back, please.

03:53.483 --> 03:55.443
There you go.

03:56.569 --> 04:00.031
- So...how is she?

04:00.073 --> 04:04.494
- Nervous, but most girls
have the same worries.

04:04.536 --> 04:07.288
After I finished, she asked me
if she seemed different.

04:07.330 --> 04:08.873
I said, "Don't worry.

04:08.915 --> 04:10.959
You're just like other girls
your age."

04:11.001 --> 04:14.129
- And...the exam?

04:14.170 --> 04:17.632
Were there any...findings?

04:19.009 --> 04:22.637
- Medically speaking,
her hymen is intact

04:22.679 --> 04:24.723
and, um,

04:24.764 --> 04:28.852
my exam was consistent
with what Jan says.

04:28.893 --> 04:32.355
There's no sign
of any sexual contact.

04:32.397 --> 04:34.441
- Are you sure?

04:34.482 --> 04:37.736
- Mrs. Broberg,
you can rest easy.

04:37.777 --> 04:40.572
Your daughter is pure snow.
[chuckles]

04:40.613 --> 04:43.533
<i>[eerie music]</i>

04:43.575 --> 04:47.537
<i>* *</i>

04:47.579 --> 04:50.415
<i>[The Lennon Sisters'</i>
<i>"Outer Space Santa"]</i>

04:50.457 --> 04:53.626
<i>* *</i>

04:53.668 --> 04:55.462
<i>- * Outer space Santa *</i>

04:55.503 --> 04:57.630
<i>* Shining up the stars *</i>

04:57.672 --> 04:59.466
<i>* Outer space helpers *</i>

04:59.507 --> 05:01.384
<i>* Packing them in jars *</i>

05:01.426 --> 05:03.261
<i>* Milky Way workshop *</i>

05:03.303 --> 05:05.138
<i>* What a busy place *</i>

05:05.180 --> 05:07.223
- Just what the doctor ordered?

05:07.265 --> 05:08.475
<i>- * For kids in outer space *</i>

05:08.516 --> 05:09.768
<i>* I dreamed I had *</i>

05:09.809 --> 05:11.978
- Did you miss Tastee Treet?

05:12.020 --> 05:14.481
<i>- * And grew,</i>
<i>I dreamed I was a pilot *</i>

05:14.522 --> 05:16.024
<i>* I flew and flew and flew *</i>

05:16.066 --> 05:18.276
- Janny?

05:18.318 --> 05:24.824
If there is...anything
that we ought to talk about,

05:24.866 --> 05:27.369
we should.

05:27.410 --> 05:28.661
- Like what?

05:28.703 --> 05:32.082
- Like places
that you and B went

05:32.123 --> 05:34.626
and what you did together
the whole time

05:34.668 --> 05:36.336
that you were in Mex--

05:36.878 --> 05:38.963
- I don't wanna talk about
this anymore.

05:39.005 --> 05:41.675
You promised
that we could move on.

05:42.926 --> 05:44.386
- We can.

05:45.887 --> 05:47.639
We will.

05:50.141 --> 05:53.061
<i>[soft melancholic music]</i>

05:53.103 --> 06:00.068
<i>* *</i>

06:25.927 --> 06:29.014
- I've been debating
whether or not to, uh...

06:30.724 --> 06:33.059
To show you something.

06:33.101 --> 06:34.561
[drawer sliding open]

06:46.740 --> 06:48.783
It's a marriage certificate.

06:48.825 --> 06:51.619
Fella at the embassy
says it's real.

06:51.661 --> 06:53.580
- Why did he ask
for her permission

06:53.621 --> 06:55.957
if he could do this
on his own?

06:58.168 --> 06:59.961
I don't understand.

07:02.047 --> 07:05.175
Do you think he really just
did it so they could come back?

07:05.216 --> 07:08.386
- I should've shown this
to you earlier,

07:08.428 --> 07:10.221
but I didn't want you
to get worked up

07:10.263 --> 07:11.973
until I knew what was what.

07:12.015 --> 07:14.434
- Dr. Rush...

07:14.476 --> 07:16.686
says Jan's okay.

07:16.728 --> 07:18.688
- One blessing is she doesn't
seem to know anything

07:18.730 --> 07:21.941
about this marriage nonsense.

07:22.567 --> 07:24.611
So now it's our job
to help her just--

07:24.652 --> 07:27.489
- Get back to normal.

07:30.241 --> 07:37.123
<i>* *</i>

07:37.165 --> 07:40.585
- Berchtold is coming back
to Pocatello.

07:41.503 --> 07:43.046
He'll probably make bail

07:43.088 --> 07:45.507
and be right back out
in the community,

07:45.548 --> 07:47.717
at least until the hearing.

07:47.759 --> 07:50.053
- Just like that?
- He should be locked up.

07:50.095 --> 07:51.596
- That's why
the hearing's crucial.

07:51.638 --> 07:53.098
We need to show
we have a strong enough case

07:53.139 --> 07:55.308
to go to trial.
- A strong enough case?

07:55.350 --> 07:56.643
He married her.

07:56.685 --> 07:58.144
- Well, he paid two people

07:58.186 --> 08:01.106
to go to some court in Mexico
and say that their names

08:01.147 --> 08:02.982
are Jan Broberg
and Bob Berchtold.

08:03.024 --> 08:06.027
It's not quite the same thing.

08:06.069 --> 08:07.737
Now, look, the fact is,
there's a whole lot

08:07.779 --> 08:10.657
that we don't know about
what happened in Mexico,

08:10.699 --> 08:13.034
and we're in a tough spot
if Jan keeps saying

08:13.076 --> 08:15.245
that he didn't do anything
wrong.

08:15.286 --> 08:18.581
- Jan doesn't lie,
a-and Dr. Rush said

08:18.623 --> 08:21.334
that he didn't lay a finger
on her.

08:21.376 --> 08:23.878
Can't imagine the state of mind
he must've been in

08:23.920 --> 08:25.296
to get those marriage papers.

08:25.338 --> 08:27.924
- Don't think about
his state of mind.

08:27.966 --> 08:30.510
Think about yours and Jan's

08:30.552 --> 08:33.054
when you face him in court.

08:34.389 --> 08:35.890
- We'll be ready.

08:35.932 --> 08:37.892
- And I hope I don't have
to remind you,

08:37.934 --> 08:40.854
you do not talk
to the Berchtolds.

08:40.895 --> 08:43.148
And you tell your girls
not to be friendly

08:43.189 --> 08:46.526
with his boys either,
even at school.

08:46.568 --> 08:48.486
- You can be sure of that.

08:48.528 --> 08:51.698
<i>* *</i>

08:51.740 --> 08:53.825
- Mary Ann?

08:55.243 --> 08:57.078
- I understand.

08:59.205 --> 09:02.167
[people talking quietly]

09:02.208 --> 09:05.128
[soft piano music]

09:05.170 --> 09:12.093
* *

09:28.860 --> 09:30.653
<i>- Dear heavenly Father,</i>

09:30.695 --> 09:35.116
I ask thee to give me a sign
on what I'm supposed to do.

09:35.158 --> 09:38.661
I know the people from another
planet are watching.

09:38.703 --> 09:41.122
I'm being good
and following all the rules

09:41.164 --> 09:42.916
and I'm making sure
not to touch

09:42.957 --> 09:45.043
my earthly father Bob.

09:46.086 --> 09:50.340
Please protect Karen
and Susan and Mom

09:50.382 --> 09:52.926
and please keep B safe

09:52.967 --> 09:56.346
and bless him
and all of the Berchtolds too.

09:57.764 --> 10:00.141
I don't wanna be vaporized.

10:00.183 --> 10:03.353
In the name of Jesus Christ,
amen.

10:05.647 --> 10:08.566
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

10:08.608 --> 10:11.152
<i>* *</i>

10:11.194 --> 10:14.197
<i>[Merle Haggard's "If We</i>
<i>Make It Through December"]</i>

10:14.239 --> 10:21.162
<i>* *</i>

10:21.204 --> 10:27.043
<i>- * If we make it</i>
<i>through December *</i>

10:27.085 --> 10:31.297
<i>* Everything's</i>
<i>gonna be all right, I know *</i>

10:31.339 --> 10:32.799
<i>* *</i>

10:32.841 --> 10:36.302
<i>* It's the coldest time</i>
<i>of winter *</i>

10:36.344 --> 10:37.679
<i>* *</i>

10:37.721 --> 10:42.892
<i>* And I shiver</i>
<i>when I see the falling snow *</i>

10:43.852 --> 10:49.441
<i>* If we make it</i>
<i>through December *</i>

10:49.482 --> 10:51.985
<i>* Got plans to be</i>
<i>in a warmer town *</i>

10:52.027 --> 10:53.862
<i>* Come summertime *</i>

10:53.903 --> 10:55.572
<i>* *</i>

10:55.613 --> 10:57.323
<i>* Maybe even California *</i>

10:57.365 --> 10:59.492
- Merry Christmas.
- You hear the latest?

10:59.534 --> 11:02.245
Berchtold got out...
<i>- * If we make it through *</i>

11:02.287 --> 11:05.623
<i>* December, we'll be fine *</i>
- Merry Christmas.

11:05.665 --> 11:08.376
[dog barks]
- Coats up, girls.

11:10.670 --> 11:12.505
- It's real chilly.

11:12.547 --> 11:14.507
Isn't it?

11:14.549 --> 11:16.009
- It's cold in here too.

11:16.051 --> 11:18.094
- It is. Is the heater out?

11:18.136 --> 11:19.179
- Hmm.

11:24.809 --> 11:27.062
- No, it's on.

11:27.103 --> 11:30.231
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

11:30.273 --> 11:35.695
<i>* *</i>

11:35.737 --> 11:37.739
- Bob?
<i>- Yup?</i>

11:37.781 --> 11:40.200
- Window's open.

11:42.494 --> 11:44.954
[hinges squeak]

11:46.623 --> 11:48.500
<i>- Was it Santa Claus?</i>

11:48.541 --> 11:50.460
<i>- Do you think</i>
<i>someone broke in?</i>

11:50.502 --> 11:52.420
<i>- Don't move.</i>

11:55.465 --> 11:58.551
<i>[moody music]</i>

11:58.593 --> 12:05.475
<i>* *</i>

12:11.940 --> 12:13.817
<i>- This is a reminder...</i>

12:13.858 --> 12:16.444
<i>of the mission.</i>

12:32.794 --> 12:34.295
[faucet running]

12:34.337 --> 12:35.755
[dishes clinking]

12:35.797 --> 12:38.174
<i>- * As his fingers *</i>

12:38.216 --> 12:42.595
<i>* Softly fall upon my face *</i>

12:42.637 --> 12:46.433
<i>* *</i>

12:46.474 --> 12:50.729
<i>* He lights the flame</i>
<i>of desire *</i>

12:50.770 --> 12:53.023
[knock at door]

12:53.064 --> 12:56.776
<i>* *</i>

12:56.818 --> 13:02.157
<i>* And love is the foundation *</i>

13:02.198 --> 13:03.992
<i>* We lean on *</i>

13:04.034 --> 13:07.328
<i>* *</i>

13:07.370 --> 13:09.539
- Gail.

13:09.581 --> 13:10.999
What are you doing here?

13:11.041 --> 13:12.459
- Can I speak to you?

13:12.500 --> 13:13.752
Alone?

13:13.793 --> 13:16.796
I'm really sorry.

13:16.838 --> 13:19.132
Bob sent me.

13:19.174 --> 13:22.218
You'll wanna hear this.

13:34.731 --> 13:37.484
How's Jan?

13:37.525 --> 13:40.070
- She's, uh, she's fine.

13:40.111 --> 13:42.781
What's this about, Gail?

13:42.822 --> 13:46.868
'Cause, um...
y-you shouldn't be here.

13:49.371 --> 13:51.706
- Well, I came over
f-for your sake.

13:51.748 --> 13:55.460
See, I'm...we've got a lawyer

13:55.502 --> 13:58.672
who's gonna fix
this whole mess.

13:58.713 --> 14:01.841
She's been helping my family,
and she'll help yours

14:01.883 --> 14:03.301
if you talk to her.

14:03.343 --> 14:05.679
- That doesn't make any sense,
Gail.

14:05.720 --> 14:07.639
Why would your lawyer help us?

14:07.681 --> 14:10.517
- You remember
Jennifer Ferguson, don't you?

14:10.558 --> 14:11.851
- I know Jennifer.

14:11.893 --> 14:14.312
She's always been
a good customer.

14:14.354 --> 14:17.899
- Well, that's
who's helping me and Bob.

14:17.941 --> 14:21.277
Jennifer thinks having
this whole mess

14:21.319 --> 14:25.073
out in public would just be
the worst thing for everyone.

14:25.115 --> 14:27.075
Think of the kids.

14:27.117 --> 14:29.452
Think of Jan.

14:29.494 --> 14:31.538
You don't wanna
put her through a trial.

14:31.579 --> 14:34.958
- I am thinking of Jan.

14:35.000 --> 14:39.713
Your husband kidnapped her
and needs to pay.

14:39.754 --> 14:41.589
End of discussion.

14:43.967 --> 14:47.887
- He's not the only one
who made an error of judgment.

14:48.304 --> 14:51.599
You and Mary Ann
knew how sick he was.

14:51.641 --> 14:53.184
But that didn't stop you

14:53.226 --> 14:55.687
from letting Jan spend...

14:55.729 --> 14:58.064
so much time with him.

14:58.106 --> 15:00.400
You practically
threw Jan at him.

15:00.442 --> 15:02.777
- We did what?
- With his therapy,

15:02.819 --> 15:06.948
his tapes, you...
you allowed that.

15:09.284 --> 15:11.953
And you know
what I'm talking about.

15:11.995 --> 15:14.039
That's what he says.

15:14.080 --> 15:16.332
And it's not just Jan.

15:18.043 --> 15:21.296
- What is that supposed
to mean?

15:21.338 --> 15:24.466
- Bob and I are very open
with each other.

15:26.926 --> 15:28.636
And he told me...

15:32.515 --> 15:34.309
What you did.

15:38.021 --> 15:40.565
But Bob says
if you aren't willing

15:40.607 --> 15:42.484
to work with Jennifer...

15:44.986 --> 15:47.947
Then it will go out in public

15:47.989 --> 15:52.369
that you are a sinful man

15:52.410 --> 15:55.538
with unnatural desires.

15:57.624 --> 16:00.126
And it would just be awful
if it did.

16:03.046 --> 16:06.007
Give Jennifer a call.

16:13.306 --> 16:16.476
<i>[low music]</i>

16:16.518 --> 16:23.441
<i>* *</i>

16:46.798 --> 16:48.508
- What did Gail want?

16:48.550 --> 16:51.845
- She asked if we would meet
with their lawyer.

16:51.886 --> 16:54.097
Jennifer Ferguson.

16:54.139 --> 16:56.891
- Oh, I-I like Jennifer.

16:56.933 --> 16:59.102
- Yeah, well, she...

17:01.896 --> 17:05.692
She has a proposal

17:05.734 --> 17:08.069
that would, uh...

17:09.696 --> 17:12.157
Make trial go away.

17:12.198 --> 17:15.368
- Trial does sound like
it'll be awful,

17:15.410 --> 17:18.329
especially for Jan.

17:18.371 --> 17:21.041
<i>[soft, intense music]</i>

17:21.082 --> 17:28.006
<i>* *</i>

17:28.048 --> 17:29.924
Bob?

17:29.966 --> 17:31.634
- [sniffles]

17:35.138 --> 17:37.015
[sniffling]

17:37.057 --> 17:38.641
[whispering] She said
horrible things, Mary Ann.

17:38.683 --> 17:42.354
She--she said horrible things
about me.

17:42.395 --> 17:43.563
- What did she say?

17:43.605 --> 17:45.774
- I'm sorry.

17:45.815 --> 17:47.233
[clears throat]

17:49.652 --> 17:53.198
- Whatever it is,

17:53.239 --> 17:55.909
it'll be all right.

17:55.950 --> 17:58.536
- I-I-I made a...

17:58.578 --> 18:02.749
terrible, terrible mistake,

18:02.791 --> 18:06.127
but I am--
I'm going to repent...

18:08.296 --> 18:10.757
And that's all you need
to know.

18:10.799 --> 18:12.884
- You're scaring me.

18:15.970 --> 18:17.889
What do you mean, mistake?

18:20.767 --> 18:24.562
- Me and Bob Berchtold...

18:27.023 --> 18:29.150
It's nothing, but...

18:31.403 --> 18:35.198
If we go to trial,
they are gonna...

18:35.240 --> 18:37.617
they're gonna say things
like-like I'm a...

18:37.659 --> 18:41.413
<i>* *</i>

18:41.454 --> 18:44.290
Like I'm a homosexual or...

18:46.584 --> 18:49.129
- Y--

18:49.170 --> 18:54.384
You...and B?

18:57.178 --> 18:59.097
I don't understand.

18:59.139 --> 19:01.099
- There's nothing
to understand.

19:01.141 --> 19:02.976
- Bob.

19:03.018 --> 19:06.271
<i>* *</i>

19:06.312 --> 19:08.148
<i>[school bell rings]</i>

19:08.189 --> 19:10.150
[kids chattering]

19:10.191 --> 19:13.111
<i>[peaceful dreamlike music]</i>

19:13.153 --> 19:18.033
<i>* *</i>

19:18.074 --> 19:20.326
- What?
- 16.

19:20.368 --> 19:24.998
<i>* *</i>

19:25.040 --> 19:27.917
- Oh, yes, it is. 60 plus 16.

19:27.959 --> 19:34.841
<i>* *</i>

19:47.896 --> 19:49.689
- Can I sit here?

19:49.731 --> 19:52.984
- You want to?
Nobody else does.

19:53.026 --> 19:55.320
- Of course I want to.

19:55.362 --> 19:58.448
I'm not supposed to
talk to you, but...

19:58.490 --> 20:00.325
I think it's okay.

20:00.367 --> 20:07.499
<i>* *</i>

20:11.336 --> 20:13.963
Aren't you hungry?
- Not really.

20:14.005 --> 20:16.174
I'm not feeling well.

20:16.216 --> 20:17.926
You can have mine if you want.

20:17.967 --> 20:21.346
- That's okay.
You might wanna eat it later.

20:25.600 --> 20:29.104
Nobody really talks to me
at all pretty much

20:29.145 --> 20:31.314
ever since I came back.

20:31.356 --> 20:34.776
- Yeah.

20:34.818 --> 20:36.319
- What?

20:36.361 --> 20:38.655
- I think they told everybody
not to talk to you about it,

20:38.697 --> 20:41.741
but they didn't let me
go to that assembly,

20:41.783 --> 20:43.535
so I dunno.

20:44.327 --> 20:46.955
- What assembly?

20:46.996 --> 20:48.331
[door clicks open]

20:48.373 --> 20:50.083
Mom.

20:50.125 --> 20:51.918
There was a whole assembly.

20:51.960 --> 20:53.586
They wouldn't let Jasper go
because they were talking

20:53.628 --> 20:56.047
to all the kids about me and B.

20:56.089 --> 20:57.590
Why did they have
to make such a big fuss

20:57.632 --> 20:59.926
that now everybody
at school treats me weird?

20:59.968 --> 21:03.096
- Janny, I'm so sorry.

21:03.138 --> 21:04.848
I hate to see you unhappy.

21:04.889 --> 21:07.642
- You said
things would be normal.

21:07.684 --> 21:09.894
[running footsteps]

21:11.813 --> 21:14.733
- I heard
from Gail again today.

21:16.735 --> 21:18.987
- I was thinking about that.

21:19.029 --> 21:21.865
<i>[soft, edgy music]</i>

21:21.906 --> 21:24.075
<i>* *</i>

21:24.117 --> 21:29.456
Maybe we should go see
Jennifer Ferguson.

21:29.497 --> 21:32.334
See what she has to say.

21:34.836 --> 21:37.422
- We could let her
do all the talking.

21:37.464 --> 21:43.386
<i>* *</i>

21:43.428 --> 21:46.890
- A trial would be bad for Jan.

21:46.931 --> 21:53.813
<i>* *</i>

21:53.855 --> 21:57.692
- We are only here
because you are a good member

21:57.734 --> 22:01.112
of the community, Jennifer,
and we--

22:01.154 --> 22:03.823
You've always been
a good customer for many years.

22:03.865 --> 22:06.576
- Well, thank you, Bob.
[laughs]

22:06.618 --> 22:08.828
Ruthie was asking about Jan,
by the way.

22:08.870 --> 22:10.330
She says hi.

22:10.372 --> 22:13.124
- Aw, that's sweet.
- Mm-hmm.

22:13.166 --> 22:17.420
- So we understand
that you have a proposal,

22:17.462 --> 22:20.507
uh, for us?
- Yeah, of course.

22:20.548 --> 22:23.426
There's a way
to avoid a public trial.

22:23.468 --> 22:26.388
It'll just require
some paperwork.

22:27.430 --> 22:29.015
- What way is that?

22:33.770 --> 22:35.772
- Uh, and what is this?

22:35.814 --> 22:39.984
- Affidavits for you
to look over and sign.

22:40.026 --> 22:42.779
You know what an affidavit is,
right?

22:42.821 --> 22:46.783
Oh, it's just legal jargon
for a statement of truth.

22:46.825 --> 22:48.868
If you sign these papers,
we can set the record straight

22:48.910 --> 22:50.954
about what happened
before Mexico.

22:50.995 --> 22:54.124
That's all I need from you
in order to settle things.

22:55.417 --> 22:57.419
- This says
that Robert Berchtold

22:57.460 --> 22:59.504
had permission to take Jan.

22:59.546 --> 23:01.923
- That's not true.

23:01.965 --> 23:07.554
- I'm sorry, but the other way
is a long, drawn-out trial.

23:07.595 --> 23:09.305
I thought you didn't want that.

23:09.347 --> 23:10.557
- But this is a lie.

23:10.598 --> 23:14.769
- A trial
will be your worst nightmare.

23:14.811 --> 23:16.771
We'll have to make a case

23:16.813 --> 23:21.401
that you're unfit parents
who endangered your children.

23:21.443 --> 23:24.738
I know you don't wanna see
your girls get taken away.

23:24.779 --> 23:26.239
- No one can do that.

23:26.281 --> 23:28.074
- I've seen it happen.

23:28.116 --> 23:34.748
And honestly, we have so much
we could say here...

23:34.789 --> 23:40.128
like how Bob suffers from
being a homosexual, for one.

23:40.170 --> 23:42.547
- I am not--
- Do you wanna swear in court

23:42.589 --> 23:43.923
under oath
that nothing sexual happened

23:43.965 --> 23:45.759
between you and Bob Berchtold?

23:47.927 --> 23:51.097
How would you feel if everyone
in the ward knew what you did?

23:51.139 --> 23:53.808
- But what you're asking us
to say is just not true.

23:53.850 --> 23:56.227
- How do you know what's true,
Mary Ann?

23:56.269 --> 23:58.938
You heard the doctors.
Even your daughter says it:

23:58.980 --> 24:01.941
nothing bad happened in Mexico.

24:02.734 --> 24:05.445
I mean, do you really want
to pull your family apart

24:05.487 --> 24:07.572
over this?

24:10.617 --> 24:14.579
Why don't you look over
these papers again?

24:16.164 --> 24:18.625
Can I get you a coffee?

24:18.667 --> 24:20.210
You don't drink coffee.

24:20.251 --> 24:22.295
Uh, how 'bout some waters?

24:22.337 --> 24:23.588
Yeah, I'll get you some waters.

24:23.630 --> 24:26.549
<i>[light percussive music]</i>

24:26.591 --> 24:31.554
<i>* *</i>

24:31.596 --> 24:33.723
- What were you thinking?

24:35.183 --> 24:36.434
Where's Allen Funt?

24:36.476 --> 24:37.644
Am I on "Candid Camera"?
- Garth.

24:37.686 --> 24:40.146
- How could you sign
a statement like that?

24:40.188 --> 24:42.315
- You don't deal
with the criminal lawyer.

24:42.357 --> 24:44.317
That's Mr. Pincock's job.

24:44.359 --> 24:46.111
He's the prosecutor.

24:46.152 --> 24:48.613
- We were just trying
to do what's best for Jan

24:48.655 --> 24:50.156
to put this all behind us.

24:50.198 --> 24:53.368
- What's best for Jan is to put
that man under the prison.

24:53.410 --> 24:55.995
- So there still
will be a trial?

24:56.037 --> 24:57.580
- If I have anything
to do with it,

24:57.622 --> 24:59.666
but you shot our case
right in the foot.

24:59.708 --> 25:01.918
- I-I'm sorry.
We didn't know.

25:01.960 --> 25:04.838
- The hearing is next week.

25:04.879 --> 25:06.631
You are going
to release statements

25:06.673 --> 25:08.174
tomorrow morning to the press,

25:08.216 --> 25:10.093
and you are gonna retract
what you said.

25:10.135 --> 25:11.886
- We are sorry
for the inconvenience,

25:11.928 --> 25:14.222
and we will do that right away.

25:16.099 --> 25:17.892
- Okay.

25:17.934 --> 25:20.020
Okay.

25:20.061 --> 25:22.313
I hate to blow my stack,
but what's done is done.

25:22.355 --> 25:25.692
Now we just need to present
the best case that we can.

25:25.734 --> 25:28.111
There will be no jury
at the hearing.

25:28.153 --> 25:29.696
You will each
give private testimony

25:29.738 --> 25:31.656
before the judge.

25:31.698 --> 25:33.116
And Mr. Berchtold, well,

25:33.158 --> 25:34.701
he's entitled
to face his accuser

25:34.743 --> 25:36.995
so he will be in the room,

25:37.037 --> 25:38.580
which reminds me,
I'm gonna need

25:38.621 --> 25:40.498
that marriage certificate
from you.

25:40.540 --> 25:43.126
- I-I sent that back to Mexico.

25:43.168 --> 25:45.503
- You did what?

25:45.545 --> 25:47.005
- To get it annulled.

25:47.047 --> 25:48.548
- You didn't send
the original document,

25:48.590 --> 25:50.592
did you?

25:50.633 --> 25:52.260
That's a key piece of evidence.

25:52.302 --> 25:54.971
Please tell me
that you have copies.

25:59.059 --> 26:01.353
- Oh, Bob.

26:03.855 --> 26:06.941
- We'll-we'll
figure something out.

26:09.694 --> 26:12.447
Mr. Pincock's office
will be in touch shortly

26:12.489 --> 26:14.366
to prepare you for the hearing.

26:14.407 --> 26:15.325
- Thank you, Pete.
- Mm-hmm.

26:15.367 --> 26:16.826
- Thank you, Mr. Pincock.

26:23.249 --> 26:24.334
[door thuds shut]

26:28.254 --> 26:29.673
- They're decent people.

26:29.714 --> 26:31.591
They're just naive.

26:31.633 --> 26:34.427
- I am a Mormon too,
Agent Welsh,

26:34.469 --> 26:37.097
but I wouldn't let some guy
do whatever the heck he wanted

26:37.138 --> 26:38.932
with my kid.

26:38.973 --> 26:40.934
- And what if that guy
is your brother?

26:40.975 --> 26:43.770
Or your best friend?

26:44.854 --> 26:48.274
- I have other cases.

26:48.316 --> 26:52.320
<i>* *</i>

26:52.362 --> 26:54.239
<i>- Dear heavenly Father,</i>

26:54.280 --> 26:58.284
I'm still waiting
on instructions

26:58.326 --> 27:01.287
from Zada and Zethra
on the mission.

27:01.329 --> 27:04.958
And also, please forgive me
for lying in court tomorrow

27:05.000 --> 27:07.836
if they ask about the pills
and the baby.

27:09.629 --> 27:14.634
Please don't let them guess
that I'm only part human.

27:14.676 --> 27:18.638
In the name of Jesus Christ,
amen.

27:18.680 --> 27:21.641
<i>[moody music]</i>

27:21.683 --> 27:28.857
<i>* *</i>

27:39.993 --> 27:42.162
- State your name.

27:42.203 --> 27:43.997
- Jan Broberg.

27:44.039 --> 27:45.832
- Do you swear
that the testimony you give

27:45.874 --> 27:47.417
will be the truth,
the whole truth,

27:47.459 --> 27:50.045
and nothing but the truth?

27:51.421 --> 27:53.631
- I do.

27:53.673 --> 27:55.133
- Have a seat.

28:03.433 --> 28:05.143
- Hey, Jan.

28:05.185 --> 28:08.063
Would you tell the court about
your relationship

28:08.104 --> 28:11.107
with Mr. Berchtold?

28:17.405 --> 28:18.907
You don't have
to look at him, Jan.

28:18.948 --> 28:20.408
You can look at me.

28:22.827 --> 28:25.080
What's your relationship
with Mr. Berchtold?

28:25.121 --> 28:28.166
<i>[soft tense music]</i>

28:28.208 --> 28:34.089
- Um, he's a really good friend
of mine.

28:36.841 --> 28:39.844
- Um...

28:39.886 --> 28:47.018
<i>* *</i>

28:53.650 --> 28:58.279
- You knew Mr. Berchtold
was unwell, didn't you?

28:58.321 --> 29:00.573
- I knew
he had various therapies,

29:00.615 --> 29:02.659
but I'm not a doctor.

29:02.701 --> 29:06.204
- Can you tell us more about
the therapy you knew of?

29:06.246 --> 29:10.125
- His psychologist
recommended it.

29:10.166 --> 29:15.797
He played these tapes
from his clinic in California.

29:15.839 --> 29:17.757
- What tapes, Mrs. Broberg?

29:17.799 --> 29:23.430
- Oh, they were just about him
being on vacation with his wife

29:23.471 --> 29:25.807
on a beach.

29:28.059 --> 29:31.312
He was supposed to...

29:33.481 --> 29:38.987
Lie beside Jan
and listen to them

29:39.029 --> 29:41.364
when she was asleep.

29:41.406 --> 29:46.786
<i>* *</i>

29:46.828 --> 29:49.164
- And you allowed this?

29:49.205 --> 29:51.124
- His doctor prescribed it,

29:51.166 --> 29:52.834
and he was never alone
with her.

29:52.876 --> 29:55.545
I would walk in the room
to put things away,

29:55.587 --> 29:58.173
and I never observed anything
unnatural going on.

29:58.214 --> 30:00.592
He was on top of the sheets.

30:01.217 --> 30:02.886
- You never thought
there was anything weird

30:02.927 --> 30:04.054
about this process?

30:04.095 --> 30:05.472
- Sure, I did.

30:05.513 --> 30:07.390
I'd never heard of this type
of therapy,

30:07.432 --> 30:14.189
but...there's a lot of things
that I've never heard of.

30:15.690 --> 30:20.445
And I accept that we have
to listen to doctors.

30:20.487 --> 30:23.823
And Mr. Berchtold was like
a part of our family,

30:23.865 --> 30:27.160
and I wanted to help him.

30:27.202 --> 30:29.913
I-I thought he needed our help.

30:31.206 --> 30:33.416
- So what do you believe now?

30:33.458 --> 30:35.585
Because you don't really have
any idea what went on

30:35.627 --> 30:37.003
in Mexico, do you?

30:37.045 --> 30:40.173
Except
what your daughter's told you.

30:40.215 --> 30:45.178
- I suppose...that's...true.

30:45.220 --> 30:47.430
- And what did she tell you?

30:47.472 --> 30:49.808
- That she and B
just went on a vacation

30:49.849 --> 30:51.393
and nothing bad happened.

30:51.434 --> 30:53.603
- And the doctors
find no evidence

30:53.645 --> 30:55.563
of anything inappropriate,
isn't that right?

30:55.605 --> 30:57.065
- Objection.
- And the allergy pills

30:57.107 --> 30:59.275
they tested were just
regular allergy pills.

30:59.317 --> 31:01.027
- Objection!
- So isn't it possible

31:01.069 --> 31:02.445
that it's just like
your daughter

31:02.487 --> 31:04.197
and all the doctors
and experts say

31:04.239 --> 31:06.157
and Mr. Berchtold
didn't do anything wrong?

31:06.199 --> 31:07.575
- Your Honor, objection!

31:07.617 --> 31:09.035
- Ms. Ferguson.

31:09.077 --> 31:11.705
- Withdrawn.

31:11.746 --> 31:14.249
No more questions.

31:16.209 --> 31:19.337
- I told Mr. Berchtold that day

31:19.379 --> 31:22.507
that he was not allowed
to take Jan.

31:22.549 --> 31:25.301
I was adamant,
and he betrayed me completely.

31:25.343 --> 31:27.053
- And what exactly
was the nature

31:27.095 --> 31:29.431
of your relationship
with my client?

31:29.472 --> 31:32.892
Would you say
you both were close?

31:32.934 --> 31:35.645
- Our families spent
a fair amount of time together.

31:35.687 --> 31:37.397
- Just your families?

31:37.439 --> 31:40.191
Or did you also spend
a lot of time one-on-one?

31:43.111 --> 31:47.574
- Now and again,
we would get together.

31:47.615 --> 31:51.786
But I will never let
Bob Berchtold anywhere near me

31:51.828 --> 31:55.582
or my family ever again.

31:55.623 --> 31:58.209
- Prior to Mexico, my client
describes your relationship

31:58.251 --> 32:01.463
to him as very close.

32:01.504 --> 32:03.423
Intimate.

32:03.465 --> 32:07.260
He says he shared a lot
of private things with you.

32:07.302 --> 32:09.971
Did you feel comfortable
being open with him?

32:13.308 --> 32:15.602
- That's all in the past.

32:16.936 --> 32:18.897
- Well,
you've signed affidavits

32:18.938 --> 32:21.733
saying you gave him permission
to take Jan on a road trip,

32:21.775 --> 32:23.485
and now
you're telling us the opposite.

32:23.526 --> 32:27.655
So how can anyone
trust your word?

32:27.697 --> 32:30.617
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

32:30.658 --> 32:32.660
<i>* *</i>

32:32.702 --> 32:33.787
- Well, the good news is,

32:33.828 --> 32:36.373
the judge is granting us
a trial.

32:36.414 --> 32:39.542
However,
you cannot take the stand

32:39.584 --> 32:41.961
in front of a jury
like you just did.

32:42.003 --> 32:43.338
- How do you mean?

32:43.380 --> 32:45.090
- You were okay, Bob.
Not perfect,

32:45.131 --> 32:47.759
but at least
you came across like someone

32:47.801 --> 32:50.595
who actually dislikes the man
who kidnapped his daughter.

32:51.304 --> 32:53.473
No more surprises.

32:53.515 --> 32:55.934
We cannot let your history
with this guy

32:55.975 --> 32:57.727
jeopardize our case.

32:57.769 --> 32:58.895
- It really didn't help

32:58.937 --> 33:01.147
that Jan denied
being kidnapped.

33:01.189 --> 33:03.900
- She's had
a difficult experience.

33:03.942 --> 33:06.111
- Well,
now that she's back home,

33:06.152 --> 33:07.570
it's important to make sure

33:07.612 --> 33:08.988
that she keeps her head
on straight

33:09.030 --> 33:11.199
when it comes to Berchtold.

33:21.793 --> 33:23.086
- Can I go get some water?

33:23.128 --> 33:25.422
- Yeah. Just right around
the corner.

33:42.897 --> 33:44.566
- Psst.

33:45.984 --> 33:48.028
Shh.

33:48.069 --> 33:51.865
<i>* *</i>

33:51.906 --> 33:54.325
Shh.

33:56.661 --> 33:58.872
You did so good in there,
Dolly.

33:58.913 --> 34:01.541
So good.

34:01.583 --> 34:05.879
You are the only person
who cares what happens to me.

34:05.920 --> 34:09.132
And we can't forget
about the mission, all right?

34:09.174 --> 34:11.259
- I'm doing everything
they ask me to.

34:11.301 --> 34:12.927
I-I promise.

34:12.969 --> 34:15.764
- Good. Good.

34:17.265 --> 34:19.851
I am so scared
what they'll do to us

34:19.893 --> 34:24.105
or our families
if we don't stick to the plan.

34:24.147 --> 34:26.024
Gosh,
I don't think I could bear it

34:26.066 --> 34:28.318
if anything happened
to my boys

34:28.360 --> 34:31.237
or if they made Susan
take your place.

34:31.279 --> 34:33.114
Could you?

34:34.866 --> 34:37.285
- I wish I knew if they were
happy with me or not.

34:39.162 --> 34:40.747
Do you think
they're still watching?

34:40.789 --> 34:42.207
- Oh, I know they are.

34:42.248 --> 34:44.084
I know they are.

34:44.125 --> 34:47.754
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

34:47.796 --> 34:49.547
In the meantime,

34:49.589 --> 34:52.258
you just gotta remember
everything we talked about.

34:52.300 --> 34:56.346
All right?
Especially stay away from Bob.

34:56.388 --> 34:58.348
Don't ever let him touch you.

34:58.390 --> 35:01.226
You understand?

35:03.103 --> 35:05.313
Dolly.

35:05.355 --> 35:09.901
<i>* *</i>

35:09.943 --> 35:11.444
[elevator bell dings]

35:25.417 --> 35:27.711
- What's wrong?

35:30.213 --> 35:33.133
- Are-are you feeling okay?

35:33.174 --> 35:36.761
- I think so. How come?

35:36.803 --> 35:38.805
- You're not sick?

35:38.847 --> 35:41.224
- No.

35:41.266 --> 35:43.143
- Are you hearing any voices?

35:43.184 --> 35:45.854
- Jan, what's wrong?

35:45.895 --> 35:49.941
- I just want you to know,
I'll protect you.

35:49.983 --> 35:51.985
- From what?

35:52.027 --> 35:54.863
- We're different, Susan.

35:54.904 --> 35:57.907
We're special.

36:02.912 --> 36:05.874
[phone rings]

36:06.916 --> 36:09.586
[ringing]

36:11.087 --> 36:12.339
- Broberg residence.

36:12.380 --> 36:14.049
<i>- What kind of parents</i>
<i>are you?</i>

36:14.090 --> 36:15.300
<i>You let that creep walk away?</i>

36:15.342 --> 36:17.385
<i>Did he kidnap her</i>
<i>or didn't he?</i>

36:25.060 --> 36:26.561
- Bob.

36:28.938 --> 36:30.357
Hey.

36:30.398 --> 36:31.858
- I need a walk.

36:39.824 --> 36:42.744
[phone rings]

36:45.080 --> 36:47.916
[ringing]

36:50.001 --> 36:51.461
- Hello, Brobergs.

36:51.503 --> 36:54.547
<i>- Mary Ann, don't hang up.</i>
<i>It's me.</i>

36:54.589 --> 36:56.925
- You're not supposed
to call here.

36:56.966 --> 36:58.343
<i>- No, I know. I just--</i>

36:58.385 --> 37:00.303
<i>I needed to hear your voice.</i>

37:00.345 --> 37:02.847
<i>You're the only one who cares</i>
<i>what happens to me.</i>

37:02.889 --> 37:04.808
<i>You saved me this week</i>
<i>at the hearing.</i>

37:04.849 --> 37:07.352
- I'm going to hang up.
<i>- Please don't. Please don't.</i>

37:07.394 --> 37:10.522
<i>Oh, it just kills me.</i>

37:10.563 --> 37:13.566
<i>It absolutely kills me</i>
<i>to think I hurt you.</i>

37:13.608 --> 37:16.444
Can you find it in your heart
to forgive me?

37:18.321 --> 37:22.784
- You'll never know
how hard that was...

37:24.452 --> 37:26.705
What you put us all through.

37:28.164 --> 37:29.749
What went on down there?

37:29.791 --> 37:32.419
Nobody will be straight
with me.

37:32.460 --> 37:34.754
<i>- Well, look,</i>
<i>I've moved to Ogden</i>

37:34.796 --> 37:36.923
'cause my brother Joe
is the only one

37:36.965 --> 37:38.925
who'll give me a job.

37:38.967 --> 37:42.178
I come back every weekend
so I can see Gail and the boys.

37:42.220 --> 37:46.891
<i>[sighs] Even if you never</i>
<i>talk to me again,</i>

37:46.933 --> 37:50.478
just getting to see your face
at church...

37:50.520 --> 37:52.605
that's all I need.

37:56.234 --> 38:02.157
But if you want me to just
answer every question you have,

38:02.198 --> 38:04.784
I'll tell you.

38:04.826 --> 38:06.703
- Go on then.

38:06.745 --> 38:08.371
Tell.

38:08.413 --> 38:10.749
- In person.

38:11.458 --> 38:13.877
<i>I need to see you.</i>

38:13.918 --> 38:15.462
I need to talk
to you face-to-face

38:15.503 --> 38:17.213
so you can understand.

38:17.255 --> 38:18.882
- I can't.

38:18.923 --> 38:21.384
- Everything I did

38:21.426 --> 38:24.304
was to be with you.

38:24.346 --> 38:26.639
Everything.

38:26.681 --> 38:29.476
To get closer to you.

38:31.394 --> 38:33.480
<i>That's the truth,</i>

38:33.521 --> 38:36.358
and don't you forget it,
Mary Ann.

38:41.279 --> 38:44.491
<i>[eerie tinkling notes]</i>

38:44.532 --> 38:46.785
- Dear heavenly Father,

38:46.826 --> 38:50.163
I kneel before thee humbly

38:50.205 --> 38:54.542
to beg for thy forgiveness
for my transgression.

38:56.961 --> 38:59.130
This guilt is...

39:01.800 --> 39:03.593
Too great.

39:05.303 --> 39:07.514
I ask thee humbly, Lord,

39:07.555 --> 39:12.686
to give me the strength...

39:12.727 --> 39:16.981
to do what I know
has to be done.

39:17.023 --> 39:20.860
[dogs barking distantly]

39:27.492 --> 39:30.120
- Bob,
I'm glad you found the strength

39:30.161 --> 39:32.539
within yourself to come to us

39:32.580 --> 39:35.542
and admit
to this transgression.

39:35.583 --> 39:40.547
Obviously, this is a matter
of great concern.

39:41.840 --> 39:43.633
After discussion and prayer,

39:43.675 --> 39:47.345
we've concluded
that a formal probation

39:47.387 --> 39:49.764
is not enough.

39:50.223 --> 39:55.395
But we do feel,
as representatives of the Lord,

39:55.437 --> 39:58.231
that because
this was a first offense,

39:58.273 --> 40:01.943
and since sexual encounters
with Brother Berchtold

40:01.985 --> 40:05.572
were not numerous,

40:05.613 --> 40:09.534
and because you show
genuine remorse,

40:09.576 --> 40:13.788
that excommunication
is not merited.

40:16.875 --> 40:19.878
We think
that your actions do merit

40:19.919 --> 40:23.757
you being disfellowshipped.

40:23.798 --> 40:26.968
Now this, above all,
is a loving process

40:27.010 --> 40:31.306
to bring you closer to God
and his plan for forgiveness

40:31.348 --> 40:33.475
and happiness.

40:35.226 --> 40:37.896
We love you, Bob.

40:37.937 --> 40:41.316
And we are here for you
as your brothers

40:41.358 --> 40:45.487
in the gospel of Jesus Christ.

40:45.528 --> 40:49.282
- In the name of Jesus Christ,
amen.

40:49.324 --> 40:51.284
all: Amen.

40:51.326 --> 40:57.290
- Uh, there's something
that I need to tell you girls.

40:57.332 --> 40:59.501
This morning I saw the bishop,

40:59.542 --> 41:02.128
and he thinks...

41:02.170 --> 41:04.047
well, we both think

41:04.089 --> 41:06.466
that maybe I shouldn't
take the sacrament

41:06.508 --> 41:08.760
for a little while.

41:08.802 --> 41:10.512
- Isn't everyone supposed to?

41:10.553 --> 41:13.139
- I didn't know you saw him.

41:13.181 --> 41:15.266
- Yes, this morning.

41:15.308 --> 41:17.227
I've been disfellowshipped.

41:17.268 --> 41:22.357
- So you just went and had
a conversation with him?

41:22.399 --> 41:25.652
- Well, I spoke with my brother
about it first.

41:27.946 --> 41:32.617
But I've cleared it up,
and we're moving on.

41:32.659 --> 41:34.703
- What's disfellowship?

41:34.744 --> 41:37.497
- It means that I can't
partake in the sacrament

41:37.539 --> 41:40.166
because I've made
some mistakes,

41:40.208 --> 41:42.377
but I will again soon.

41:42.419 --> 41:46.131
As long as I keep going
to church and be good,

41:46.172 --> 41:49.134
I can take it again.

41:49.175 --> 41:52.220
<i>[somber music]</i>

41:52.262 --> 41:56.516
<i>* *</i>

41:56.558 --> 41:59.561
- I'm sorry, Dad.

42:04.399 --> 42:07.193
Heavenly Father, I'm very sorry

42:07.235 --> 42:09.946
I touched my earthly father
Bob's arm at dinner.

42:09.988 --> 42:12.741
It was just for a second
so please, please

42:12.782 --> 42:15.994
don't let the people
from another planet hurt me

42:16.036 --> 42:18.913
or let Susan take my place.

42:18.955 --> 42:22.876
I don't want anyone else
to suffer because of me.

42:22.917 --> 42:25.879
And please
don't let them hurt Karen

42:25.920 --> 42:30.133
or any of the Berchtolds
either.

42:30.175 --> 42:31.801
Amen.

42:31.843 --> 42:35.847
- Brothers and sisters,
before we begin,

42:35.889 --> 42:39.351
I'd like to ask us all to pray
for Jasper Berchtold

42:39.392 --> 42:42.228
and the Berchtold family.

42:42.270 --> 42:45.273
Jasper has been taken
with a very sudden

42:45.315 --> 42:47.776
and confounding illness

42:47.817 --> 42:51.196
that the doctors
are still trying to diagnose.

42:51.237 --> 42:53.073
[congregation whispering]

42:53.114 --> 42:58.411
So please,
do keep them in your thoughts.

42:58.453 --> 43:01.331
[whispering continues]

43:07.837 --> 43:09.547
- I made Jasper
a get well basket,

43:09.589 --> 43:11.091
and I wanna take it over.

43:11.132 --> 43:12.926
I just need
to tell him I'm sorry.

43:12.967 --> 43:14.594
- Wait,
you think it's your fault

43:14.636 --> 43:15.929
that he got sick?

43:15.970 --> 43:18.098
That doesn't make any sense.

43:18.139 --> 43:20.600
- You always say show charity
when people get sick.

43:20.642 --> 43:23.311
- You're not going over there.

43:32.654 --> 43:34.781
- What?
We were told not to interact

43:34.823 --> 43:36.616
with the Berchtolds, Mary Ann.

43:36.658 --> 43:39.077
- B won't even be there.

43:39.119 --> 43:40.829
He has to go back to Ogden
for work.

43:40.870 --> 43:42.789
He's probably halfway back
by now.

43:42.831 --> 43:44.708
- We're supposed
to cut off all contact

43:44.749 --> 43:46.459
with the whole family.

43:46.501 --> 43:49.421
- Jasper and the other children
haven't done anything wrong,

43:49.462 --> 43:52.257
and we have to decide
what's right for us, Bob.

43:52.298 --> 43:55.677
- Well, than this one's
an easy decision to make.

43:55.719 --> 43:57.887
- Children
shouldn't be punished

43:57.929 --> 44:01.349
for their parents' mistakes.

44:14.863 --> 44:17.782
- Well, come in.

44:21.369 --> 44:23.580
I wasn't expecting you.

44:23.621 --> 44:26.541
- Jan made this for Jasper.

44:26.583 --> 44:28.918
- Oh, my goodness.

44:31.212 --> 44:33.715
She truly does have
the biggest heart.

44:33.757 --> 44:35.800
Jasper will be so touched.

44:35.842 --> 44:37.802
I'll bring it to him.
I go back to the hospital

44:37.844 --> 44:39.721
tomorrow morning.

44:39.763 --> 44:42.223
- I'll leave you.
- No!

44:42.265 --> 44:43.725
Please?

44:45.935 --> 44:49.147
<i>- * And I know that someday *</i>

44:49.189 --> 44:51.649
- The doctors say
it might be something

44:51.691 --> 44:54.903
called "infectious neurosis."

44:54.944 --> 44:57.405
He just woke up and...

44:59.115 --> 45:00.867
Couldn't move his legs.

45:00.909 --> 45:03.703
We had to lift him down
from the top bunk.

45:03.745 --> 45:07.332
I mean,
thank heaven Bob was here.

45:07.374 --> 45:09.876
He had driven up
the night before for church.

45:09.918 --> 45:11.753
- Oh, my goodness.

45:11.795 --> 45:15.215
I'm so sorry for Jasper.

45:15.256 --> 45:19.844
- All I can think about
is what else I can do,

45:19.886 --> 45:22.722
how I can make him well.

45:22.764 --> 45:24.974
- When our children
are in pain,

45:25.016 --> 45:29.771
it's hard to think
of anything else.

45:32.857 --> 45:34.526
- I've missed talking to you.

45:38.196 --> 45:42.409
- [laughs] I tried to make
your meat loaf recipe.

45:42.450 --> 45:44.244
It wasn't the same.

45:45.286 --> 45:48.123
- Well, I'll make it for you.

45:49.582 --> 45:51.126
Anytime.

45:53.878 --> 45:56.548
Mary Ann, I have to tell you...

45:58.967 --> 46:01.928
Bob just feels so bad.

46:01.970 --> 46:04.222
This whole thing
has wrecked him.

46:04.264 --> 46:07.267
- I can't talk about all that.
- He's desperate to apologize.

46:07.308 --> 46:11.771
I--I've never seen him
like this.

46:11.813 --> 46:16.609
But I know how badly he wants
to make things right with you.

46:16.651 --> 46:19.612
<i>[soft, moody music]</i>

46:19.654 --> 46:26.578
<i>* *</i>

46:45.263 --> 46:51.978
- I think I'm gonna go visit
my mother in Garland tomorrow.

46:58.777 --> 47:02.447
<i>[moody, lilting music]</i>

47:02.489 --> 47:08.536
<i>* *</i>

47:49.828 --> 47:51.746
- I knew you'd come.

47:51.788 --> 47:54.165
- I can only stay a short time.

47:54.207 --> 47:57.377
My mother's expecting me
for dinner.

47:57.419 --> 48:00.171
- Whatever you say, Mary Ann.

48:00.213 --> 48:03.633
- I want you to tell me
what went on down there.

48:03.675 --> 48:05.260
The truth.

48:07.929 --> 48:10.098
Why don't you come inside?

48:10.140 --> 48:12.934
I know how cold you get.

48:12.976 --> 48:14.352
Come on.

48:33.288 --> 48:36.041
Here you go.
- No.

48:36.082 --> 48:38.001
- All right.

48:45.633 --> 48:47.135
[door slams shut]

48:48.511 --> 48:51.890
Ah, gosh.

48:51.931 --> 48:53.475
You look so wonderful.

48:53.516 --> 48:54.934
- Oh, no.

48:54.976 --> 48:56.728
Stop all that.

48:56.770 --> 49:00.273
- You're right, yeah.

49:00.315 --> 49:03.193
You just have so much goodness
in you.

49:03.234 --> 49:07.197
- I'm here because
I need to understand.

49:07.238 --> 49:11.826
Help me understand
what went on in Mexico.

49:11.868 --> 49:15.789
And why you got
those marriage papers with...

49:15.830 --> 49:17.582
with you and Jan.

49:17.624 --> 49:20.502
- Well, dang it, Mary Ann.
You know why.

49:20.543 --> 49:24.506
It's because Bob
called the FBI.

49:24.547 --> 49:27.133
We had to get married on paper,

49:27.175 --> 49:28.760
'cause we both wanted
to come back.

49:28.802 --> 49:30.553
Otherwise I'd spend
the next ten years

49:30.595 --> 49:32.847
in a Mexican jail, fightin'
to get back to the States.

49:32.889 --> 49:34.808
- Is that true?

49:34.849 --> 49:36.476
- Hell yes it's true!

49:36.518 --> 49:38.353
That's why I never even
told her about it.

49:38.395 --> 49:40.730
I didn't want her to think
we'd actually gotten married.

49:40.772 --> 49:43.566
That'd be a little weird.
[laughs] Wouldn't it?

49:44.818 --> 49:47.737
Mary Ann...

49:51.032 --> 49:53.410
It's a piece of paper.
[small laugh]

49:57.706 --> 50:00.750
I just had to find a way
to get her back home to you

50:00.792 --> 50:02.210
without getting locked up.

50:02.252 --> 50:04.129
- I'm still so upset.

50:04.170 --> 50:06.464
I could just about kill you.

50:06.506 --> 50:08.133
- [laughs]

50:08.174 --> 50:11.678
You know, Mary Ann,

50:11.720 --> 50:15.473
you have ruined my life.

50:16.725 --> 50:19.686
Ever since
I first laid eyes on you.

50:19.728 --> 50:21.855
Oh, hell.

50:21.896 --> 50:24.274
I may as well confess it.

50:27.318 --> 50:29.779
You're the one I wanted
to run away with.

50:32.240 --> 50:34.868
I love you.

50:34.909 --> 50:36.786
And only you.

50:38.163 --> 50:40.540
But you--you're--

50:40.582 --> 50:43.043
you're just so damned devoted.

50:43.084 --> 50:47.213
- What about Gail and Bob?

50:47.255 --> 50:49.299
- Bob doesn't deserve you.

50:49.341 --> 50:51.217
I feel bad for him,

50:51.259 --> 50:53.428
for the burden he carries.

50:53.470 --> 50:56.264
He's a homosexual, you know.
- No, he's not.

50:56.306 --> 50:58.767
I know my husband.

50:58.808 --> 51:01.186
- Will you sit down?

51:01.227 --> 51:03.104
Please?

51:09.611 --> 51:12.614
You just make me nervous
[laughs]

51:12.655 --> 51:17.452
standing here like you're gonna
up and go.

51:29.297 --> 51:32.509
Let me make something hot
for you to sip on.

51:46.147 --> 51:48.274
[sighs] You know, every time

51:48.316 --> 51:51.653
I saw her standing here
cooking...

51:53.780 --> 51:55.824
I imagined it was you.

51:55.865 --> 51:58.618
Everything she did,

51:58.660 --> 52:02.372
it just reminded me how much
I wanted to be with you.

52:05.000 --> 52:08.336
[sighs]

52:14.551 --> 52:16.970
It opened up
something inside me, Mary Ann,

52:17.012 --> 52:20.598
about the way I felt

52:20.640 --> 52:23.852
and the way I feel for you.

52:25.895 --> 52:28.189
I can't lose you again.

52:31.026 --> 52:33.903
I can't.

52:33.945 --> 52:36.990
<i>[soft, uneasy music]</i>

52:37.032 --> 52:40.910
<i>* *</i>

52:40.952 --> 52:42.620
- [inhales sharply]

52:57.010 --> 52:59.012
[melancholic country music]

52:59.054 --> 53:01.556
- Do you remember Henry's Lake?
- [laughs softly]

53:01.598 --> 53:04.684
- Two summers ago,
you'd hop up on those skis

53:04.726 --> 53:08.438
and then you'd be like
a princess on the water?

53:08.480 --> 53:11.358
You were my star.

53:11.399 --> 53:14.152
- I wish I knew
where all the time went.

53:14.194 --> 53:17.697
- Oh, I know. I know.

53:17.739 --> 53:21.242
- We can't put back
all the pieces.

53:23.578 --> 53:26.664
[The Hollies'
"The Air That I Breathe"]

53:26.706 --> 53:29.376
* *

53:29.417 --> 53:33.254
- I always think of you
when I hear this song.

53:33.296 --> 53:36.800
- It's one
of my favorite tunes.

53:36.841 --> 53:38.760
* *

53:38.802 --> 53:43.973
- * If I could make a wish *

53:44.015 --> 53:46.935
* I think I'd pass *

53:46.976 --> 53:51.731
- Where's my sweet Mary Ann
gone?

53:51.773 --> 53:54.484
Wouldn't this be
the perfect life?

53:54.526 --> 53:57.570
You and the girls
could move down here,

53:57.612 --> 54:01.074
and we'd be our own family.

54:01.116 --> 54:05.245
Have a life full of vacations,

54:05.286 --> 54:10.250
sunshine, laughter, and love.

